The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 09 February is 211,583 (24,386.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 04 February, there were 10,246 new confirmed cases (1,180.9 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 28 January, there were 11,181 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 8% (935 fewer cases).
